caption: The current menu is different than what is listed, but it's pretty similar. I got the chicken quesadillas, and they were really good. Mamy and Maleka are so welcoming and FUN.  I eat lunch at this location 2-3 times a week and they always greet me with a smile, they know what I like, and make me feel like an old friend the moment I step into the restaurant.  The food is good too.  :-)

I absolutely love getting lunch here when I'm on campus. The staff is so attentive of you and your requests and the food is super good. Mami is literally the best by asking how my day is going and always encourages me to do great in school. Absolutely love it.

willys is definitely a 100/10 experience and enjoyed every detail about that place. the management is second to none and they are very nice

It's a Willy's, so the food is pretty standard - reliable, quick Tex-Mex without many surprises. It's the staff that really shines at this establishment though. I usually come here during conventions or conferences downtown, so the place is swamped. The staff have always been efficient and friendly though, even though they must be absolutely overwhelmed with the number of customers coming through. The dining area is also usually clean and quiet, making it a perfect respite.

I went to willy's after a depressing day at school and i do not regret it. The beans and rice is to die for and the colorful veggies turned my day from a bad one to a one to remember. The staff show respect and passion in serving this food that i believe was made in heaven.

Am a freshman at Georgia state university and am here from 8am to 9 pm everyday. Willys is restaurant on campus that cooks food that makes me feel at home. The burritos they have remind me of the burritos my grandmother used to make as a kid. I will definitely be recommending this place to my friends and family.
Always a good experience! The staff is amazing and Jerell makes the best nachos. If you’re on campus, stop by and grab a bite!

Mami is the best. I am a frequent customer at Georgia state  wiillys and I always look forward to speaking with this employee. She is always the quickest, most helpful and friendly server. When she is not there, a decline in service is notable. Outstanding!

The service and food are always great! Mami always has a smile in her face,  her customer service is top notch. She is knows how to keep the line moving. She is wonderful. They need to have many more employees like her.

Mami is especially friendly and talkative with her customers, and knows multiple regular orders by heart (including my own). I definitely recommend this location for a quick, tasty meal at a fair price.

The service never disappoints. The workers are friendly and quick. Trina is the sweetest lady ever. I see her talking to more customers than just myself and I love coming in before or after my class for the fresh and delicious food!

Wonderful staff, great food, perfect location. Nothing better than that.

I appreciate this Willy's for many things, not the least of which are staff that are friendly, tasty food, and convenience to work.  That said, there are aspects I don't like about this location, and mostly it's tied in with online/call in orders.  These always seem to come in at the middle of the lunch rush and are somehow given priority over the people in line - or that's the appearance of what happens, I could be mistaken. But even that wouldn't be the issue except somehow my order always gets messed up when I'm there for one of these. Not inedibly messed up, just...I end up with the wrong meat, or an ingredient I asked not to have. By the time I'm aware of this, I'm back at my office, and I'm not going to walk back down to point out the issue.  Now, is this going to stop me from going there?  No, probably not - again, it's not inedible mistakes, just irritating ones.

Sits on Georgia State campus close to Grady Hospital

Nachos is great. i like the crew also catches my attention to enter this restaurant. keep it up guys

Each team member was completing a task as they helped the small stream of customers. The next time I am in the Ga State area I will again frequent this location as I was overall pleased with my experience. Keep up the great work Willys staff :-)

I walked in to this establishment and was immediately taken by an employee who was sweeping the food prep area and this brought joy to me b/c I can honestly saying after visiting many restaurants I cant remember one where I saw the employees cleaning.  This should be a given but it is not.  I was so impressed I gave the manager Ms. Vanessa the compliment and I also went over and gave the girls who were cleaning the same compliment, many times you hear all the complaints of the things you are not doing right or could have done better but today was a good day for the team at 100 Piedmont.  I have not walked into a fast casual Mexican restaurant and not seen a salsa bar that did not have salsa on the bar.  This place was damned near spotless - which means their doing something right - having the LARGE population of clients they deal with from GA State, all the Capital and City employees down the block and all the additional take-out and walk in clients to be this busy and still have time to clean and keep a remarkable staff is an achievement.  Kudos to you Ms. Vanessa and the team at 100 Piedmont, keep up the good work!!!!!!!!   : )

The guy was so rude even when i told him it was my first time. He automatically put shredded cheese on my nachos even though i didnt want shredded cheese. I know at Moes they always ask you. Next the short Hispanic lady was SO rude. One, i could not understand her she spoke so fast so i said "im sorry what ?" And she got mad and was just rude. I was scared to ask for anything. I quickly just told her lettuce and cucumbers because i was scared to ask for other stuff. She just threw lettuce and cucumbers on my plate like a mean lunch lady. I could tell she hates her job. She was horrible. The cashier didn't even ask if i wanted a drink . i told her can we add a drink please. To get my drink, the sweet tea was so sweet. It tasted like SYRUP! ugh. And then THE WHOLE SODA MACHINE WAS FLAT! the coke, sprite everything came out flat. So i paid for a drink but got water. Next i couldn't even finish my food it was terrible. At least at moes i feel welcomed and their food is so much better and i have never been sick after eating at moes. Like I said this was my first experience but my last. I find this ridiculous considering the price of a handful of lettuce is much cheaper than the combined cost of chips, tortillas, beans, and rice. Was a little extra lettuce really that big of a deal that you had to lose a customer over it? I will not be coming back to this restaurant.

They really don’t realize that it’s the customers why they are able to have a job. While I know that me not eating there ever again won’t put a dent in their sales...I don’t care.
